com.atherys.quests.api.objective

Class AbstractObjective<T extends org.spongepowered.api.event.Event>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.atherys.quests.api.objective.AbstractObjective<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The event class this objective listens for
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Observer, Prototype, Objective, org.spongepowered.api.text.TextElement, org.spongepowered.api.text.TextRepresentable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DialogObjective, InteractWithBlockObjective, ItemDeliveryObjective, KillEntityObjective, ReachLocationObjective

    public abstract class AbstractObjective<T extends org.spongepowered.api.event.Event>
extends java.lang.Object
implements Objective
    An abstract implementation of Objective which checks whether or not the Objective's event corresponds to the event being supplied via notify(Event, Quester).
    This is the preferred method for introducing new Objectives, as any such would require code of this sort to filter out irrelevant events. This class does nothing more than abstract away the necessary boilerplate.
